{"type":"message","id":"b20c7b83","parentId":"9e68f95f","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:00:16.166Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"2050\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"6053576134\",\n  \"sender\": \"Khương Nịnh\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-04-13 06:46 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Khương Nịnh (6053576134)\",\n  \"id\": \"6053576134\",\n  \"name\": \"Khương Nịnh\",\n  \"username\": \"khuowgn\"\n}\n```\n\nUsing docker image sha256:7015f2c475d511a251955877c2862016a4042512ba625ed905e69202f87e1a21 for docker:24.0.5 with digest docker@sha256:3c6e4dca7a63c9a32a4e00da40461ce067f255987ccc9721cf18ffa087bcd1ef ...\n$ apk add --no-cache git\nfetch https://dl-cdn.alpinelinux.org/alpine/v3.18/main/x86_64/APKINDEX.tar.gz\nfetch https://dl-cdn.alpinelinux.org/alpine/v3.18/community/x86_64/APKINDEX.tar.gz\n(1/9) Installing brotli-libs (1.0.9-r14)\n(2/9) Installing libunistring (1.1-r1)\n(3/9) Installing libidn2 (2.3.4-r1)\n(4/9) Installing nghttp2-libs (1.57.0-r0)\n(5/9) Installing libpsl (0.21.5-r0)\n(6/9) Installing libcurl (8.12.1-r0)\n(7/9) Installing libexpat (2.7.0-r0)\n(8/9) Installing pcre2 (10.42-r1)\n(9/9) Installing git (2.40.4-r0)\nExecuting busybox-1.36.1-r2.trigger\nOK: 41 MiB in 64 packages\n$ git config --global --add safe.directory $PRJ_PATH\n$ cd $PRJ_PATH\n$ git reset --hard HEAD\nHEAD is now at e4eff59 Merge branch 'fix/missing-login-by-token-api' into 'develop'\n$ git clean -fd\n$ git pull https://gitlab-ci-token:${CI_JOB_TOKEN}@${CI_SERVER_HOST}/${CI_PROJECT_PATH}.git develop\nFrom https://gitlab.com/ahv-dtlx/ahv-qlhv-fe\n * branch develop -> FETCH_HEAD\nhint: You have divergent branches and need to specify how to reconcile them.\nhint: You can do so by running one of the following commands sometime before\nhint: your next pull:\nhint: \nhint: git config pull.rebase false # merge\nhint: git config pull.rebase true # rebase\nhint: git config pull.ff only # fast-forward only\nhint: \nhint: You can replace \"git config\" with \"git config --global\" to set a default\nhint: preference for all repositories. You can also pass --rebase, --no-rebase,\nhint: or --ff-only on the command line to override the configured default per\nhint: invocation.\nfatal: Need to specify how to reconcile divergent branches.\nCleaning up project directory and file based variables\n00:02\nERROR: Job failed: exit code 128"}],"timestamp":1776063616010}}
{"type":"message","id":"d491be47","parentId":"b20c7b83","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:00:29.121Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a different pipeline failure - this is from the FE (ahv-qlhv-fe) pipeline, not the BE. The error is in the git pull step:\n\n```\ngit pull https://gitlab-ci-token:${CI_JOB_TOKEN}@${CI_SERVER_HOST}/${CI_PROJECT_PATH}.git develop\nfatal: Need to specify how to reconcile divergent branches.\n```\n\nThe `.gitlab-ci.yml` uses `git pull` without specifying `--ff-only`, and the local branch has diverged from origin/develop. This is exactly the commit that khuong ninh made: `fix(ci): add --ff-only to git pull to prevent divergent branches`\n\n\nThe commit title suggests the fix should have addressed this issue, so I need to check if it's actually deployed or if something went wrong with the deployment.","thinkingSignature":"6e48332a2b15fbe9f84f32025657a41a57cbb6968bc2e8880689ce1589da4c40"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_swutjd8u4sil_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"https://gitlab.com/api/v4/projects/81078350/pipelines?per_page=3\" -H \"PRIVATE-TOKEN: glpat-c_N4qQVxbcktRro-S5rdwGM6MQpvOjEKdTpoZDBsYg8.01.170axqn65\" 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json\ndata=json.load(sys.stdin)\nif isinstance(data, list):\n    for p in data:\n        print(f'Pipeline {p[\\\"id\\\"]} | {p[\\\"status\\\"]} | {p[\\\"ref\\\"]} | {p[\\\"created_at\\\"][:16]}Z')\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":716,"output":338,"cacheRead":50032,"cacheWrite":2402,"totalTokens":53488,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776063616167,"responseId":"062bc781b53426ce1cf1e6dc65130d59"}}
