{"type":"message","id":"0dd8f663","parentId":"e521931d","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:00:43.055Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the latest pipeline (2448220987) is running on `develop` branch, and the previous one (2448193908) failed. Let me check if the MR was from develop -> develop or what.\n\nWait, the MR title says \"!9 to merge fix/ci-git-pull-ff-only\" but that was for BE (project 81078323). The Lead's message shows the git pull error from what looks like FE (docker image, Alpine apk install).\n\nLet me check what MR !9 is - it might have been re-triggered or there's another issue.\n\nActually wait - the Lead pasted the error log which shows it's running on FE's CI (docker:24.0.5, Alpine git install). \n\nNow I need to figure out which MR is actually failing and whether the --ff-only fix was applied correctly to the gitlab-ci.yml configuration.","thinkingSignature":"54f1583b277b7bc980ae8e98fb514b3e82d929b2868f6ff729a3b5bf39ddffb9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qpa1aagnzs5o_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check what MR is failing - look at the FE MRs\ncurl -s \"https://gitlab.com/api/v4/projects/81078350/merge_requests?state=opened&per_page=10\" -H \"PRIVATE-TOKEN: glpat-c_N4qQVxbcktRro-S5rdwGM6MQpvOjEKdTpoZDBsYg8.01.170axqn65\" 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json\nmrs=json.load(sys.stdin)\nfor mr in mrs:\n    p = mr.get('head_pipeline', {})\n    print(f'MR !{mr[\\\"iid\\\"]} | {mr[\\\"source_branch\\\"]} | pipeline:{p.get(\\\"status\\\",\\\"none\\\")} | {mr[\\\"web_url\\\"]}')\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":200,"output":387,"cacheRead":52085,"cacheWrite":1298,"totalTokens":53970,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776063630030,"responseId":"062bc78fb744358b927b09d4673e3c00"}}
