{"type":"message","id":"82a7abb2","parentId":"6f8fae32","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:57:20.996Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"These workspaces are ecosystem infrastructure repos, not the actual project code repos. When agents work on QLHV/DTLX projects, they clone the actual project repos. The git config needs to be set in those project workspaces or globally.\n\nLet me set git config globally for the agents, so when they clone and work on any repo, they'll use their agent name as the commit author. The workspace directories are just documentation/config workspaces, not the actual project repos.\n\nI should set global git config or set it in the specific project directories. Let me check if there are project directories.\n\nActually, the agents clone repos on-demand. The git config needs to be set at the global level so all git operations use the agent's identity.","thinkingSignature":"85ecaea02a546a784c1ba0063090af571234f219a80b59cb253b378ab8c704ae"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yzwxsxqpax5o_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Set global git config so ALL repos use agent identity\ngit config --global user.name \"Orbis (master-orchestrator)\" \ngit config --global user.email \"orbis@openclaw.ai\"\n\n# Check current commits in master-orchestrator repo\ncd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review && git log --oneline -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":322,"output":247,"cacheRead":68745,"cacheWrite":344,"totalTokens":69658,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776067031757,"responseId":"062bd4d9e76dd70b648a7f62b83c0870"}}
