{"type":"message","id":"5b5656bc","parentId":"3ec5fff3","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:57:34.309Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. The global git config is set for Orbis. But other agents will have their own sessions and may need their own git config. I should create a script or set up the git config for each agent.\n\nLet me also set the git config for the project workspaces (QLHV BE/FE) since agents will work there.\n\nBut actually, the key question is: when agents work on actual project repos (like ahv-qlhv-be), where do they clone those repos? I saw that I cloned ahv-qlhv-be into /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-qlhv-be earlier. Let me check.\n\nThe issue is each agent runs in its own session/workspace. When they `git clone`, they'll use their own git config. Since agents are spawned with their own workspace directory, I need to ensure each agent's workspace has the correct git config.\n\n\nI should verify whether the workspaces directory already has git repos set up that I need to configure.","thinkingSignature":"af8a022c0e895c40508d75ab6388175d1fa135ecb30eaf159b05576e78d18330"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cogkyrsi0ggu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check where project repos are cloned\nls /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ 2>/dev/null | head -10\necho \"---\"\n# Also set global for root (covers all future clones)\ngit config --global user.name \"Orbis (master-orchestrator)\" \ngit config --global user.email \"orbis@openclaw.ai\"\ngit config --global --list | grep user"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":217,"output":306,"cacheRead":68879,"cacheWrite":674,"totalTokens":70076,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776067041366,"responseId":"062bd4e29c18f94d22503eed41549d1f"}}
