{"type":"message","id":"2b4ffe9e","parentId":"478d201d","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:57:43.307Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The global git config is set for Orbis. But when other agents (senior-backend, senior-frontend) are spawned, they'll have their own workspace and may not have this git config set.\n\nThe key is: when an agent clones a repo and commits, it will use whatever git config is set in that environment. The best approach is to set global git config so all agents use their own identity.\n\nBut actually, the real solution is simpler: set git config globally for the whole system, and each agent's spawned session will inherit that config. Or set it per-workspace.\n\nLet me also set the git config for the ahv-qlhv-be repo (which Orbis cloned earlier).","thinkingSignature":"0d793b753d31afa3826e90bf993f197c4358c2506121be9b80f79e999f3adb4b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vnmzj5hg2ysm_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Set git config for the cloned project repo\ngit -C /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-qlhv-be config user.name \"Orbis (master-orchestrator)\" 2>/dev/null\ngit -C /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-qlhv-be config user.email \"orbis@openclaw.ai\" 2>/dev/null\necho \"✅ ahv-qlhv-be git config set\"\n\n# Also check AHV Works repos\nls /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ | grep -i ahv"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":192,"output":281,"cacheRead":69301,"cacheWrite":670,"totalTokens":70444,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776067054778,"responseId":"062bd4f045343c039e6a9bea2cca71e2"}}
