{"type":"message","id":"20f83682","parentId":"340ea74f","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:39:57.722Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the sessions:\n\n1. Direct (Lead) - KEEP\n2. QLHV group (-5163901258) - ALREADY ENDED ✅\n3. DTLX group (-5168104492) - ALREADY ENDED ✅\n4. Cron sessions - KEEP\n5. AHV Works group (-5212380728) - not showing as active\n\nThe QLHV and DTLX group sessions are already ended. Lead wants to only work on ahv-dtlx-backend and ahv-qlhv-frontend. Wait, Lead said \"ahv-dtlx-backend, ahv-dtlx-frontend\" - that's DTLX. \n\nBut the DTLX group session has ended too, so I need to figure out what Lead actually wants to keep active versus what to stop. Looking at the active sessions, the cron jobs are fine to keep, but I should clarify whether the DTLX ecosystem group needs to be restarted or if Lead just wants me to focus on those two specific projects without maintaining the group session.","thinkingSignature":"54f14f309d01c62991c21d36697f4f10f20cf2cacb62658531bbcd920ec83353"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_05802v2hzg7y_1","name":"sessions_history","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5168104492","limit":3}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":4057,"output":271,"cacheRead":114314,"cacheWrite":369,"totalTokens":119011,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776134378378,"responseId":"062cdbec714904fa169c119ed65b7edb"}}
