{"type":"message","id":"afcf237f","parentId":"6a9f097a","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:19:11.252Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the problem clearly now:\n\n1. The subagent `cd3256cb` is using the **TroLy model** and getting 500 `providerSpecificData` errors - this is the exact same error as before\n2. The DTLX group (-5168104492) just ended again (at 03:02 UTC)\n3. Multiple backend subagents are failing with the same 500 error\n\nThe root issue is clear: **The TroLy model (`AHV-Holding-TroLy`) is broken** - it keeps returning 500 errors about `providerSpecificData`. The agent is being spawned with the TroLy model instead of the DEV model.\n\n\nThe issue traces back to the workspace configuration for `senior-backend` - it's configured to use `AHV-Holding-TroLy` as the default model, which is why all those subagents are hitting the same error. I need to override the model to `AHV-Holding-DEV` instead, or fix the agent configuration itself.","thinkingSignature":"fd6f7ae2d0a3afcb5cec8325099c5e5f92e2bdf2cd160e2023f7cb2fce837106"},{"type":"text","text":"**Vấn đề rõ ràng:** Model `AHV-Holding-TroLy` đang bị lỗi — trả về 500 error `providerSpecificData` trên mọi request.\n\n```\n500 {\"error\":{\"message\":\"Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'providerSpecificData')\"}}\n```\n\nTất cả backend subagents đều dùng TroLy → tất cả fail.\n\nOrbis fix ngay bằng cách override model:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_57njurp4ucdo_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /root/.openclaw/agents/senior-backend/agent/config.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import sys,json; cfg=json.load(sys.stdin); print('model:', cfg.get('model','not set')); print('defaultModel:', cfg.get('defaultModel','not set'))\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"config not found\"\nls /root/.openclaw/agents/senior-backend/agent/ 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":2003,"output":437,"