{"type":"message","id":"20baa3fe","parentId":"147ca8d3","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:20:22.999Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The agents section is empty in openclaw2.json too. The default model must be set at the provider level or in the sessions.json itself. Since the sessions.json contains model preferences per session, and the sessions are created by spawning subagents with the agent's default, the issue might be in how the agent was configured when it was first set up.\n\nLet me check if there's a `defaultModel` field anywhere at the provider or account level. Actually, looking at this more carefully - the sessions.json entries all have model overrides. Maybe the agent itself stores a default model somewhere.\n\nWait - let me look at this differently. The agent `senior-backend` has its own `models.json` which has both TroLy and DEV models available. \n\nSo the real issue is that the agent's default model got switched to TroLy, which is causing all the 500 errors on the backend. I need to track down where that default is being set - it's likely in the openclaw.json at the global or account level.","thinkingSignature":"dc23e89d653628ccac4bba380c684c7ca8d7a8720418a09b70f1aa5f5cff51bf"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3u6z65wkt3pt_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /root/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\ncfg = json.load(sys.stdin)\nprint('defaultModel:', cfg.get('defaultModel', 'not set'))\nproviders = cfg.get('providers', {})\nahv = providers.get('ahvholding', {})\nprint('ahvholding defaultModel:', ahv.get('defaultModel', 'not set'))\nprint('ahvholding keys:', list(ahv.keys()))\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":122,"output":325,"cacheRead":133747,"cacheWrite":462,"totalTokens":134656,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776140412776,"responseId":"062